description: The female pedestrian was struck by car whose driver has been arrested for dangerous driving.
title: Leeds: Woman killed in Alwoodley crash
title_page: Leeds: Woman killed in Alwoodley crash - BBC News
maintext:
A woman has died following a collision between a car and a pedestrian.
The incident happened on Harrogate Road in Alwoodley, Leeds, at 12:29 GMT on Monday, according to West Yorkshire Police.
The 81-year-old victim was taken to hospital with serious injuries but died a short time later.
A man has been arrested on suspicion of causing death by dangerous driving.
